---

<ToolLayout
  title="PDF Splitter - Split PDF into Separate Pages | Webutilbox"
  description="Split PDF files into individual pages or page ranges online. Extract specific pages from any PDF. Free browser-based PDF splitter — no upload."
  canonical={canonical}
  ogImage="https://webutilbox.com/assets/og/og-pdf-tools.svg"
  keywords="pdf splitter, split pdf, extract pdf pages, pdf separator, divide pdf"
  h1="📄 PDF Splitter"
  subtitle="Split PDF files into separate pages or extract specific page ranges."
  lastUpdated=""
  shareText="Free%20online%20PDF%20Splitter%20on%20Webutilbox.%20Privacy-focused%2C%20runs%20100%25%20in%20your%20browser."
  shareUrl={canonical}
  embedUrl={canonical}
  embedTitle="PDF Splitter - Split PDF into Separate Pages -- Webutilbox"
  embedHeight={600}
  toolCss={true}
  jsonLd={jsonLd}
>

<div class="workspace">
            <!-- Upload Area -->
            <div style="text-align: center; padding: 40px; border: 2px dashed var(--border); border-radius: 12px; background: var(--light); margin-bottom: 20px;">
                <div style="font-size: 3rem; margin-bottom: 15px;">??</div>
                <input type="file" id="pdfFile" accept=".pdf" style="display: none;" onchange="loadPDF()">
                <button class="btn btn-primary" onclick="document.getElementById('pdfFile').click()" style="padding: 15px 30px; font-size: 1rem;">
                    Select PDF File
                </button>
                <p style="margin-top: 10px; font-size: 0.85rem; color: var(--gray);">Choose a PDF file to split</p>
            </div>

            <!-- PDF Info & Options -->
            <div id="pdfOptions" style="display: none;">
                <!-- PDF Info -->
                <div style="background: var(--light); border-radius: 12px; padding: 20px; margin-bottom: 20px; border: 1px solid var(--border);">
                    <h3 style="font-size: 1rem; margin-bottom: 15px;">PDF Information</h3>
                    <div style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(150px, 1fr)); gap: 15px;">
                        <div>
                            <div style="font-size: 0.8rem; color: var(--gray); margin-bottom: 5px;">File Name</div>
                            <div id="fileName" style="font-weight: 600; word-break: break-all;"></div>
                        </div>
                        <div>
                            <div style="font-size: 0.8rem; color: var(--gray); margin-bottom: 5px;">Total Pages</div>
                            <div id="totalPages" style="font-weight: 600; font-size: 1.2rem; color: var(--primary);"></div>
                        </div>
                        <div>
                            <div style="font-size: 0.8rem; color: var(--gray); margin-bottom: 5px;">File Size</div>
                            <div id="fileSize" style="font-weight: 600;"></div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <!-- Split Options -->
                <div style="background: var(--light); border-radius: 12px; padding: 20px; margin-bottom: 20px; border: 1px solid var(--border);">
                    <h3 style="font-size: 1rem; margin-bottom: 15px;">Split Options</h3>
                    
                    <!-- Mode Selection -->
                    <div style="margin-bottom: 20px;">
                        <label style="font-size: 0.9rem; margin-bottom: 10px; display: block; font-weight: 600;">Split Mode</label>
                        <select id="splitMode" onchange="updateMode()" style="width: 100%; padding: 12px; font-size: 1rem;">
                            <option value="all">Split into individual pages</option>
                            <option value="range">Extract specific page range</option>
                            <option value="custom">Extract specific pages</option>
                        </select>
                    </div>

                    <!-- Range Input (hidden by default) -->
                    <div id="rangeInput" style="display: none; margin-bottom: 20px;">
                        <label style="font-size: 0.9rem; margin-bottom: 10px; display: block; font-weight: 600;">Page Range</label>
                        <div style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr auto 1fr; gap: 10px; align-items: center;">
                            <input type="number" id="startPage" min="1" placeholder="Start" style="padding: 10px; text-align: center;">
                            <span style="color: var(--gray);">to</span>
                            <input type="number" id="endPage" min="1" placeholder="End" style="padding: 10px; text-align: center;">
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <!-- Custom Pages Input (hidden by default) -->
                    <div id="customInput" style="display: none; margin-bottom: 20px;">
                        <label style="font-size: 0.9rem; margin-bottom: 10px; display: block; font-weight: 600;">Page Numbers</label>
                        <input type="text" id="customPages" placeholder="e.g., 1,3,5-7,10" style="width: 100%; padding: 12px;">
                        <p style="font-size: 0.8rem; color: var(--gray); margin-top: 5px;">Enter page numbers separated by commas. Use dash for ranges (e.g., 1,3,5-7,10)</p>
                    </div>

                    <button class="btn btn-success" onclick="splitPDF()" style="width: 100%; padding: 15px; font-size: 1.1rem;">
                        ?? Split PDF
                    </button>
                </div>
            </div>

            <!-- Progress -->
            <div id="progress" style="display: none; background: var(--light); border-radius: 12px; padding: 20px; border: 1px solid var(--border); text-align: center;">
                <div style="font-size: 2rem; margin-bottom: 10px;">?</div>
                <div id="progressText" style="font-size: 1rem; color: var(--gray);">Processing PDF...</div>
            </div>
        </div>

        
        <!-- Share Bar -->




<script src="/js/pdf-splitter.js" defer></script>

<div class="info-section" slot="info">
<h2>PDF Splitter - Extract and Separate PDF Pages Online</h2>
            <p>Our free PDF Splitter lets you break apart any PDF document into individual pages or extract exactly the pages you need. Whether you want to isolate a single page, pull out a range, or split an entire document into separate files, this tool does it all directly in your browser with no uploads required.</p>
            <p>It's fast, private, and works offline. Load your PDF once and split it as many times as you need without ever sending your file to a remote server.</p>

            <h3>What Is a PDF Splitter?</h3>
            <p>A PDF splitter is a tool that takes a multi-page PDF document and separates it into smaller files. You can split every page into its own individual PDF, extract a specific range of pages (for example, pages 3 through 7), or cherry-pick individual pages by number (such as pages 1, 4, and 9).</p>
            <p>This is the reverse operation of a PDF merger. Where a merger combines files, a splitter divides them. Both operations are essential for anyone who regularly works with PDF documents in professional, academic, or personal contexts.</p>
            <p>This tool runs entirely in your browser using the pdf-lib JavaScript library. It reads your PDF locally, processes the page extraction on your device, and delivers the output files as instant downloads — all without any server involvement.</p>

            <h3>PDF Splitting Options</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>Split a PDF into individual single-page files with one click</li>
                <li>Extract a continuous page range (e.g., pages 5 to 12) as a new PDF</li>
                <li>Extract specific non-consecutive pages using comma-separated input (e.g., 1, 3, 5-7, 10)</li>
                <li>Displays total page count and file size after loading</li>
                <li>Preserves original PDF quality, fonts, and formatting in all output files</li>
                <li>Works completely offline after the page has loaded</li>
                <li>No watermarks, no file size limits, no account required</li>
            </ul>

            <h3>How to Use the PDF Splitter</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>Step 1: Click "Select PDF File" and choose the PDF you want to split from your device.</li>
                <li>Step 2: The tool will display the file name, total page count, and file size so you can confirm it loaded correctly.</li>
                <li>Step 3: Choose your split mode — split all pages into individual files, extract a page range, or extract specific pages by number.</li>
                <li>Step 4: If using range or custom mode, enter the page numbers or range you want to extract.</li>
                <li>Step 5: Click "Split PDF" and the output files will download automatically to your device.</li>
            </ul>

            <h3>When to Split a PDF File</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>Extracting a single important page from a large report or contract</li>
                <li>Separating a scanned multi-page document into individual page files for filing</li>
                <li>Pulling out specific chapters or sections from a long PDF book or manual</li>
                <li>Isolating invoice pages from a combined billing statement</li>
                <li>Extracting form pages from a multi-form PDF package</li>
                <li>Splitting a presentation PDF into individual slide files for editing</li>
                <li>Removing unwanted pages by extracting only the pages you want to keep</li>
            </ul>

            <h3>Splitting PDFs Precisely</h3>
            <p>When using the custom page input, you can combine individual page numbers and ranges in a single entry. For example, entering "1, 3, 5-8, 12" will extract pages 1, 3, 5, 6, 7, 8, and 12 into a single output PDF in that order. This gives you precise control over exactly which content ends up in your output file.</p>
            <p>If you need to split a very large PDF into many individual pages, be aware that your browser will trigger multiple downloads — one per page. Some browsers may ask for permission to download multiple files at once. Allow this when prompted to ensure all pages are saved.</p>
            <p>Password-protected PDFs cannot be split until the password is removed. If your PDF is encrypted, use a PDF unlock tool first, then return here to split it. Also note that page numbers in this tool are 1-indexed, meaning the first page is page 1, not page 0.</p>

            

            <h3>PDFs Processed Locally — Never Uploaded</h3>
            <p>PDF splitting runs in your browser. Your files are never uploaded to any server.</p>
        
            <h3>Frequently Asked Questions</h3>
            <div class="faq-list">
                <div class="faq-item">
                    <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">Can I split a PDF into individual pages?</button>
                    <div class="faq-answer"><p>Yes. Upload your PDF and choose to split every page into a separate file, or specify a page range to extract. Each resulting PDF can be downloaded individually or as a ZIP archive.</p></div>
                </div>
                <div class="faq-item">
                    <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">Can I extract specific pages from a PDF?</button>
                    <div class="faq-answer"><p>Yes. Enter the page numbers or ranges you want to extract (e.g., 1-3, 5, 8-10). The tool creates a new PDF containing only those pages. This is useful for extracting chapters, sections, or specific pages from a large document.</p></div>
                </div>
                <div class="faq-item">
                    <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">Does splitting a PDF reduce quality?</button>
                    <div class="faq-answer"><p>No. Splitting only reorganizes pages into separate files. The content of each page is unchanged. Text, images, and formatting are preserved exactly as in the original.</p></div>
                </div>
                <div class="faq-item">
                    <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">What is the maximum PDF size I can split?</button>
                    <div class="faq-answer"><p>There is no hard size limit, but very large PDFs (100MB+) may be slow to process in the browser since all processing happens client-side. For very large files, a desktop tool may be more practical.</p></div>
                </div>
                <div class="faq-item">
                    <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">Can I split a password-protected PDF?</button>
                    <div class="faq-answer"><p>No. Password-protected PDFs cannot be processed without the password. Remove the password protection first, then split the file.</p></div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="related-tools">
                <h3>Related Tools</h3>
                <div class="related-tools-grid">
                    <a href="../pdf-merger/" class="related-tool-link">PDF Merger</a>
                    <a href="../pdf-images-converter/" class="related-tool-link">PDF and Images Converter</a>
                    <a href="../image-compressor/" class="related-tool-link">Image Compressor</a>
                    <a href="../image-format-converter/" class="related-tool-link">Image Format Converter</a>
                    <a href="../base64-encoder/" class="related-tool-link">Base64 Encoder</a>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
</div>

</ToolLayout>